The deprecation warning `execute(Params...)` is deprecated as of API 30 (Android 11) refers to `AsyncTask.execute()`. `AsyncTask` was deprecated in Android 11 (API 30) because it mixes threading, lifecycle concerns, and result delivery in ways that are prone to misuse. The Android documentation recommends using `java.util.concurrent` (ExecutorService) or Kotlin coroutines instead.

Here's how to replace your `Soket_AsyncTask` usage with `ExecutorService`:

```java
// In your MainActivity class
private ExecutorService executor = Executors.newSingleThreadExecutor();

// Replace the AsyncTask with this method
private void executeSSHCommand(String ip, int port, String command) {
    executor.execute(() -> {
        try {
            // Your SSH implementation here (using JSch, etc.)
            // Perform the network operation
            String result = "Command executed";

            // Update UI on main thread
            runOnUiThread(() -> {
                // Handle result in UI
                Toast.makeText(MainActivity.this, result, Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show());
            });
        } catch (Exception e) {
            runOnUiThread(() -> {
                // Handle error
                Toast.makeText(MainActivity.this, "Error: " + e.getMessage(), Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show());
            });
        }
    });
}

// Updated onClick listener
btnUp.setOnClickListener(new View.OnClickListener() {
    @Override
    public void onClick(View v) {
        // Use the entered IP address or default
